'''''Eureka''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[science fiction]] [[television series]] set in a town inhabited almost entirely by geniuses. In the UK, it is known as '''''A Town Called Eureka'''''.
The Sci-Fi Channel has renewed ''Eureka'' for a third season of 13 episodes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/tvnews.php?id=37751 |title=Coming Soon - SCI FI Orders More Eureka and Truth|date=2007-09-27 |work=Coming Soon |accessdate=2007-09-28}}</ref> To what extent this will be affected by the [[2007-2008 Writers Guild of America strike]] is unknown, although co-creator and Executive Producer Jaime Paglia has stated that it could in fact result in a larger order than the original 13 as a way to "help offset the financial impact of the production push."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.visiteureka.net/news.html?nid=190 |title=Paglia: Could the Strike Result in More Episodes? |date=2008-02-09 |work=VisitEureka.net |accessdate=2008-02-13}}</ref>
